profile_positions.description:
- Write articles for The Maastricht Diplomat - a newspaper published by the Journal Committee of the United Nations Student Association;
- Design and maintain the current Maastricht Diplomat website.
- Example articles are "The Economics of Sustainable Cannabis Trade" and "The Delicacy of Quoting The N-Word"

- Recommend to the Leaderboard the theme of the Youth Unity Model United Nations Conference of 2020, the committees of the conference, and the agenda of each committee;
- Coordinate a team of 5 people to prepare relevant documents for the conference such as but not limited to background guides for chosen committees and handbook for participants;
- Successfully advocate for and coordinate the application of UN4MUN Rules of Procedure instead of the conventional UNA-USA Rules of Procedure.
- Collaborate with the Head of Communication Department to produce academic posts on the organization's Facebook Page regarding current issues such as but not limited to Black Lives Matter and Pride Month.

- Co-found Youth Unity Model United Nations in 2018 at Vinh City, Nghe An;
- Work with the Leaderboard to select the conference's main theme and committees; 
- Manage a team of 6 people to produce relevant documents such as but not limited too chosen committees' background guides and handbook for delegates.
